OK the UDP Communication error was NOT an issue related to Podman.

It was a wrong setup of the Bind / Named DNS Nameserver.

I had
```
// Unencrypted
listen-on-v6 port 53 { ::1; };
listen-on port 53 { localhost; 127.0.0.1; 192.168.1.3; any; };

// DNS over TLS
listen-on-v6 port 853 tls letsencrypt-tls { ::1; };
listen-on port 853 tls letsencrypt-tls { localhost; 127.0.0.1; 192.168.1.3; any; };
```

If you change the ipv6 to listen to `any` then it works ...
```
// Unencrypted
listen-on-v6 port 53 { ::1; any; };
listen-on port 53 { localhost; 127.0.0.1; 192.168.1.3; any; };

// DNS over TLS
listen-on-v6 port 853 tls letsencrypt-tls { ::1; any; };
listen-on port 853 tls letsencrypt-tls { localhost; 127.0.0.1; 192.168.1.3; any; };

```
